# .claude deny-block (template/v1.29.0): ignore the whole .claude/ dir EXCEPT
# the committed cloud carrier + hooks/commands/agents. CONTENTS form (.claude/*)
# is mandatory — a dir-form `.claude/` would make the `!` negations silent
# no-ops (git cannot re-include a path under an ignored DIRECTORY). Keeps
# settings.json + hooks/commands/agents trackable while ignoring
# settings.local.json and other local-only .claude/ state.
# The leading `!.claude/` re-includes the directory itself FIRST, so the
# negations below still fire when a parent ignore shadows .claude/ — e.g. a
# developer whose GLOBAL ~/.gitignore ignores `.claude/`. Without it, git
# can't re-include a path whose parent dir is excluded, the carrier is
# silently un-add-able, and MD-09 / CLAUDE-SETTINGS-PLUGIN-BLOCK red-X in CI
# while local check.sh passes. No-op without such a global ignore.
!.claude/
.claude/*
!.claude/settings.json
!.claude/hooks/
!.claude/commands/
!.claude/agents/

# Per-archetype
